@Hikari Link: You keep asking for reads, allowing the excuses to pile up, and admitting that there's no real threat via a willingness to lynch (or even vote).  The linked post attempts to a gain favorable perception by directly telling him you believe him to be town, and by stating a belief that Smear is "most likely scum" without a previous mention of suspicion (after wanting to wait for his return and explanation) after Guy_Named_Riggs had laid down the first vote on him.<br>
<br>
<br>
I began to type an overview of my reads, but I'd rather not give Guy_Named_Riggs something to lazily mimic; he's lynchable.  I'll give you this, we have definitely have tonight to let Smear attempt to prove his role; he's off the table IMHO.
